node.text:
Today (8/8th) is the New Moon in Leo and also occurring at the peak of the Lion’s Gate Portal opening - aligning the moon with the sun, Earth, Sirius and the Galactic centre. It’s a very potent shift and a very powerful time to not only manifest and invite higher vibrational energies in , but also to explore your new energetic potential from a higher consciousness by shedding and releasing limiting behaviours and the patterns/program you have been living within for generations.
It’s an opportunity to HEAL and tune in to UNCONDITIONAL LOVE on the deepest possible level.
~
You may think all of this is hippie dippie shiz, and that's okay - no judgement! But I got suddenly inspired this afternoon and wanted to make a quick little casual yoga practice for you that you can use to first, shift and work through any stagnant energy you may be holding in your physical body. Then I invite you to light a candle (fire, for Leo season..? groundbreaking haha) pull out your favourite crystals, burn some incense or use some essential oils in a diffuser, sit in stillness a while, then work on journalling...
I used these questions for journaling today (you may like to do the same or something else completely):
First I wrote myself a love letter (as suggested by @spiritdaughter - she's an extraordinary source of knowledge, love and insight for all things spiritual and moon/cosmo related btw!) 
Then answered four prompts:
1. What would you like to heal in your life?
2. What are your releasing?
3. What does your heart want? (not your head.. your HEART)
4. Manifest8ion - What are you continuing to nourish and nurture?
~
P.s Remember to open your heart. x

node.title: 20min Grounding Yoga - 8/8 New Moon in Leo X Lions Gate Portal

After teaching class this morning, I wanted to film a little bit for you to do at home too! (I apologise for the terrible audio - I just filmed on my phone!)

(P.s I'm teaching the next few sunday mornings 8-9:30 - come and say hi and get your flow on with me!) 
xx

node.text:
I call this flavour “The Spirunilla” 🙈 
It’s Spirulina and Vanilla Vegan Protein Powder... and seriously YUMMY!!
And i’m not sure what I call the painting, except a wonderful waste of time 🤗🦋
If you haven’t connected with your creativity lately (your inner child who can dream in vivid colour and has zero limitations) then I highly recommend it! Whether it be trying a slightly unusual (but it definitely works!!) smoothie flavour or getting messy with the paints or craft kit - you will not regret it! 🙈🤗
P.s full ingredient list it:
- frozen bananas
- baby spinach
- medjool dates
- almond milk
- @tropeaka Spirulina 
- @tropeaka Vanilla Protein
- topped with raw cacao nibs
•
I use @tropeaka because it’s a brand I love and trust wholeheartedly! It’s 100% Plant Based, Vegan, Gluten Free, Organic and has a five star health rating (and it’s bloody delicious!)✨
You can use the code “Sjana15” on the @tropeaka website for 15% off your first purchase! 🙈💚🤗
•

node.text:
I miss this group of women sooo much! There is something so special and sacred about the connections you make and friendships you create with others when on a yoga retreat. It’s as if the veil of illusion from life, the ego and stress all dissipate. And all that’s left is unwavering presence and the harmony of hearts beating in unison.
Flashback to a retreat I hosted end of last year in the Byron Hinterland...
•
Stay tuned, I may have dates for another retreat being released very soon! 🙈 
•
Song and music by: @thenewlanguageband @steezy_daniels 
(Epic work on this btw - love the new song!)
Video by: @dead_parasite 
@aweventurer

node.title: Flashback to my last Yoga Retreat 💛

This is a practice created specifically for beginners, anyone wanting a gentler practice or as a humbling opportunity to come back to the foundations and find old poses in new ways ✨🦋
We take time to consciously arrive on our mats, connect to our breath, open up the physical body and embody each posture with awareness and intention. 
Thank you for joining me - I loved sharing this live with you! 
Sjana x
Also it’s 11:11 here now - divine timing or what?! ❤️🤗

node.text:
I understand this may make some people uncomfortable. And that’s completely okay if it does. 
But i’m tired of playing small (and watching others do the same) in the hopes of “not offending” anyone. 
This is what my meditation practices have looked like recently. Some more primal, some less so. 
I’m growing increasingly connected and attuned to my femininity and just what that FEELS like in the body in each moment. (And this song, “Be Here Now” by one of my dear friends @clareuchima is just PHENOMENAL for this kind of embodiment practice and out now on all music channels!) 💛
My breath is my anchor, and breathing audibly and sighing helps me release stagnant energy and rebalance my throat chakra. 
(This is the PG version for IG, but It’s quite liberating to allow yourself to really be HEARD and primal). 
I encourage you to try too.
It can be deep breaths, groans or grunts, singing or chanting... doesn’t matter what it is, or if it’s different every time! 
I am also a very tactile person. My love language is physical touch. And rather than waiting for someone else to show me affection, I give it to myself. There are obviously many ways to do this, and I could go on about the difference between “masturbation” and “making love to yourself”, (even though both serve well at different times!) but this post isn’t for that. This is about the tickle of fingertips to skin and being able to touch yourself where needed. 
I find lightly caressing my skin with my fingertips helps me to truly start to embody the here and now. And not just hugging but HOLDING myself also helps often. 
Using self touch/massage to push out and shift anything stuck (personally I love massaging my heart space, and releasing anything that is attached but no longer helpful. Or for my ladies, massaging your own breasts) has become a gamechanger. I’m witnessing myself as my own powerful energetic alchemist.
Again, there’s no right or wrong.
This is a practice of embodiment. Seperate from the ego, detached from the sense of control and sunken deep within the fluid and creative feminine. 
I move through phases, then sit in stillness and integrate until I feel called to move again.

node.text:
When you find the stagnant energy, sit with it for a moment. Explore it. Where it comes from, and what it is trying to communicate to you. 
Then, let it move through you and for you.
How?
For me, it depends what the energy is...
If it’s mental, I try meditate or do breathwork. 
If it’s physical, I need to shift it through my body - run, scream underwater in the ocean, yoga, invert, walk, dance, shake, hula hoop or masturbate.
If it’s emotional, I find that making thing with my hands helps - arts and crafts, clay play, cook/bake, journalling pen to paper, or playing with sand in my palms. And anything in nature or water seems to help a lot too. (Taking a bath, sitting in or by a pool of water and even taking a shower) 
But lately i’ve had a sensation or energy that I can’t shift. And i’m not sure exactly what it is, or why it’s seemingly so stubborn. 
It makes me question if it’s lingering for a reason... Trying to teach me something important, or guide me in uncovering something I have either forgotten, desensitised to or been oblivious to my whole life. 
It’s easy for me to write something about it, or to blame it on the moon or a planet being in retrograde or something... but choosing to sit with it, and being confronted with it indefinitely is consuming and honestly incredibly exhausting... and i’m feeling a little lost and misguided lately. I know it’s a divine redirect, but in the “now”that’s hard to comprehend at times. 
so that’s my truth and how i’m currently feeling. 
I wanted to open up this space for you to share whatever is on your mind too. How is your heart feeling? 
And do you feel like taking a moment to vent and express with radical honesty and vulnerability will help? If so, have at it. Give yourself permission to release that which no longer serves you, to make more room for that which will. Indulge and soften in to the spaciousness that is surrender, to witness what is. Please be kind and hold that same space for others. Don’t express to receive external acknowledgement, but be open to the the idea that your honesty might liberate someone else from their own illusions whilst simultaneously detaching you from your own. 💛

node.title: How are you REALLY? How is your heart?

🎉 GIVEAWAY TIME !!

To celebrate International Peace Day today (Sept 21st) I’ll be giving away some of my “Teach Peace” sustainable tees 🤗🎉

To enter, simply:
1. Like this post and and tag someone to win a tee for the each of you (5x2 tees to be won)!
 2. Make sure you’re following @sjanaelise
3. Bonus entries if you share to your story

Enter as many times as you like, the winners (and their friends!) will be randomly generated and announced on my story in 48hrs! 
🙈

P.s I’m also hosting an IG Live Meditation and Gentle Yoga today at 2pm AEST in dedication of International Peace day and the Full Moon ✨ (check count down timer in my stories for exact time for your location) 💛
Hope to see you there! All levels are welcome!! 🧘🏼‍♀️

My first sunset at my new place 🙈✨ the first of many! 
My cheeks literally hurt from smiling so much lately!!! 
I’m in love with the whole energy of this new world i’m in! And I think I quite possibly live in THE kindest community in the entire world!!! 🙈🥰🤗 
Still slowly unpacking and there is SO much to do! But i’m grateful for every second!

node.text:
Sleep is proven to be one of the best ways to improve our overall health and wellbeing, yet it is often one of the most neglected. 
I’m ALL FOR a good morning routine to prime yourself for the rest of the day! But i’m also the first to admit i’ve not been giving the same attention or INTENTION to my pre-sleep routine! 
So, i’ve decided to spice up the night time schedule with a few easy things to make a good nights rest the top priority 🌙 and help to turn on the off switch!
✔️ Investing in a mattress that helps you fall asleep faster and stay asleep for longer! (I just got the new Koala Soul Mate mattress which feels like an actual cloud! Plus it has a zip+flip option if you prefer a firmer mattress top!)
✔️ Nimble X Koala Move To Snooze Set - it’s buttery soft, breathable and super stretchy! Which makes it perfect for those pre-bed rituals as well as catching some zzz’s!
✔️ Pre-Sleep yoga and stretches! (This can be on or off your mattress and helps to remove extra tension in the body
✔️ A cup of Herbal Tea
✔️ Dimming the lights
✔️ Limiting or stopping screen time
✔️ Reading a book
✔️ Journaling - get it all OUT so you have an empty mind when it comes time to shut your eyes
✔️ Essential oils (my favourite bed time essential oil is lavender - in the diffuser and a bit on my wrists, neck and soles of the feet)
 
@koala @nimbleactivewear #sponsored #ad #sleepwithkoala #movewithnimble

node.text:
I have an ANNOUNCEMENT !🎉🤗
•
A few weeks ago I hinted at some exciting news I had to share with you! 
And to be honest, I haven’t known how to… Mostly because I don’t want it to come across as insensitive, as I’m more than aware of the heavy happenings around the world right now.
•
My news, is that I bought my first house!!! (Aka i’m now a proud mortgage owner haha). 🏠
•
I don’t move in for a few weeks yet, and it’s not anything crazy fancy - It’s old and bits are broken and falling apart and there’s a wasp nest under the deck, but it’s MY falling apart house 🤗 and I want to hopefully renovate and turn this house into a home ✨
•
After arguing against myself as to whether or not to share this with you, I decided I would. 
Because owning my own home is something i’ve been dreaming about since I was a little girl. And something I have been working towards for YEARS. 
•
I want this to be a feel-good project for me to have and to share with you, and I hope you’ll come along for the ride! 🤗☀️💛 
It’s important not to invalidate the hardship, but of equal importance is not to invalidate the good things too!
•
Society tells us that you need a partner to buy a house with and then start a family.. but at least for now, I’m doing it alone. And although I know almost NOTHING about any of this, i’m willing to make plenty of mistakes and learn along the way 🙈
•
Now more than ever, when everything seems to be unpredictable and unsure, we should be celebrating the wins - big or small! As having something that brings is a sense of joy and hope is of vital importance 💛
•
So if you have something you’re proud of (no matter how big or small!!) and want to celebrate, share it below in the comments you your success can be our shared success! ❤️❤️
•
Pics by @olivianachle 

P.s happy first day of Spring!

So yesterday was an EPIC day for a few reasons:
1.  9 Perfect Strangers launched on @primevideoaunz and i’ve been looking forward to it since I heard about it a few months ago !! 🙈🤗
2. To celebrate the launch in lockdown Amazon Prime sent me a big box FULL of my favourite things so I could make my own little DIY “wellness retreat” at home in lockdown!! 🌻✨ (a blender, yoga mat, candles, healthy snacks, a robe… everything I could possible need to enjoy a day of wholesome activities!)
3. It was Friday (FriYAY!) which means it’s now the weekennndddd and the perfect excuse to binge watch the first 3 episodes 😝
•
I watched them all yesterday and am already hooked! 🙋🏼‍♀️
It’s even cooler because the retreat centre it’s filmed at is in Byron and i’m hosting my next yoga retreat there this coming January!! How wild haha!! 🙈
#NinePerfectStrangers #ad
